<span id="freeTextContainer8557820245683427335">Well, I really raced through that one, didn&apos;t I? Why did I even start this memoir? I didn&apos;t know who this man was before I read a book review in the St. Louis Post Dispatch. So the proximity of his living just across the river might have something to do with it I suppose. What amazed me was that this man could have emerged from that horror show of a family. Good thing his grandmothers were at least caring. But that father...... Henry somehow manages to find and realize a really loving woman with</span>
  <span id="freeText8557820245683427335" style="display:none">Well, I really raced through that one, didn't I? Why did I even start this memoir? I didn't know who this man was before I read a book review in the St. Louis Post Dispatch. So the proximity of his living just across the river might have something to do with it I suppose. What amazed me was that this man could have emerged from that horror show of a family. Good thing his grandmothers were at least caring. But that father...... Henry somehow manages to find and realize a really loving woman with a really loving family; but the road before would not have indicated he would be so fortunate.<br />I'm sharing this with my sister in law who is a memoir maven. I need to talk to someone about this book.</span>
